// @test: typecheck-fail
// @tier: 0
// @level: L0
// @tags: red-team-2, round-2-2.3, nested-generics, recursion-limit, dos
// @timeout: 30000
// @description: Round-2 §2.3 (Nested generics 100 levels deep) — adversarial-depth
//   guardrail. The type-checker has a hard `ast_to_type` recursion-depth cap
//   (currently 64).  Annotations exceeding the cap MUST surface as a typed error
//   ("recursion limit exceeded: ast_to_type recursion depth exceeded") rather
//   than overflowing the host stack with a SIGSEGV.  This file pins the
//   rejection at depth 65+ so a future refactor can't accidentally remove the
//   bound (which would re-open the DoS vector: a hostile .vr file with deep
//   generics could crash the type-checker).
//
// Pre-fix surface: 100-deep `Maybe<Maybe<…>>` could in principle stack-overflow
// the recursive type-walker.  Defense: hard depth cap returns
// `recursion limit exceeded` from `ast_to_type`, propagated as a compile error.
//
// Cross-reference: companion pass-case at `vcs/specs/L0-critical/red_team_round_2_confirmations.vr`
// §2.3 covers depth 32 (well within bounds) — together they pin the
// DEFENSE CONFIRMED interval [≤64 OK, ≥65 graceful-fail].

// 65-level Maybe<…<Int>…> — one above the type-checker's recursion limit.
// The signature alone (regardless of body) drives `ast_to_type` past the cap.
fn deep_generic_overflow()
    -> Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<
       Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<
       Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<
       Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<
       Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<
       Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<
       Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<
       Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<Maybe<
       Maybe<Int
       >>>>>>>>
       >>>>>>>>
       >>>>>>>>
       >>>>>>>>
       >>>>>>>>
       >>>>>>>>
       >>>>>>>>
       >>>>>>>>
       > {
    None
}

fn main() {
    let _ = deep_generic_overflow();
}
